com.io7m.jtensors

Class VectorI4I

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.io7m.jtensors.VectorI4I
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    VectorReadable2IType, VectorReadable3IType, VectorReadable4IType

    @Immutable
public final class VectorI4I
extends Object
implements VectorReadable4IType

    A four-dimensional immutable vector type with integer elements.

    Values of this type are immutable and can therefore be safely accessed from multiple threads.

      • interpolateLinear

        public static VectorI4I interpolateLinear(VectorReadable4IType v0,
                                          VectorReadable4IType v1,
                                          double alpha)
                                   throws ArithmeticException
        Linearly interpolate between v0 and v1 by the amount alpha. The alpha parameter controls the degree of interpolation, such that:
        • interpolateLinear(v0, v1, 0.0, r) -> r = v0
        • interpolateLinear(v0, v1, 1.0, r) -> r = v1
        Parameters:
        v0 - The left input vector.
        v1 - The right input vector.
        alpha - The interpolation value, between 0.0 and 1.0.
        Returns:
        (1 - alpha) * v0 + alpha * v1
        Throws:
        ArithmeticException - Iff an internal arithmetic operation causes an integer overflow.
        Since:
        5.0.0

      • projection

        public static VectorI4I projection(VectorReadable4IType p,
                                   VectorReadable4IType q)
                            throws ArithmeticException
        Calculate the projection of the vector p onto the vector q.
        Parameters:
        p - The left vector
        q - The right vector
        Returns:
        ((dotProduct p q) / magnitudeSquared q) * q
        Throws:
        ArithmeticException - Iff an internal arithmetic operation causes an integer overflow
        Since:
        5.0.0
